name: Nature & Architecture of the Unseen pt.3
description: Like the serpent eating its own tail, technology brings the newest developments under our noses and at the same time, it becomes unseen in the process. The way kids use “high-tech” is as natural as using a door, a stair, a bulb or house heating. It is invisible. The moment unbelievable technological dreams are achieved, they become completely unnoticed. Artwork by Lucas Mateluna @Lucas.Mateluna
